frameDefinitions: An Entity has ceased to exist.
In the course of history, an Event or Entity is taken to have importance or significance.
An Author creates a Text, either written, such as a letter, or spoken, such as a speech,  that contains meaningful linguistic tokens, and may have a particular Addressee in mind.
This frame concerns a specific subset of Instances of a Type which are evaluated in terms of their similarity to a conceptual prototype of the Type.
An Entity is well-known among a wide range of people (in general or in a particular domain) for a particular Reason, which may be a behavior, characteristic, or some other associated item.
This frame contains words for individuals, i.e. humans, who are governed by virtue of being registered in a certain Jurisdiction.
frameExamples: Throughout the campaign activists have <t>made</t> financial <t>history</t> as one by one major corporations have yielded to protester power
I <t>penned</t> a letter concerning racism to Congress.
Shakespeare was <t>famous</t> during his life because he performed in front of Queen Elizabeth I more than anyone else.
listRoleDefinitions: Concrete or abstract entity that does not exist after the event.
A point at which the <fen>Entity</fen> (saliently) does not exist.
This is the Place where the <fen>Entity</fen> (saliently) does not exist.
This role identifies the event which occurs to create history.
This role identifies the entity, concrete or abstract.
This role identifies the time when the event occurs.
This role identifies where the event takes place.
The entity which results from the act of writing or speaking.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> at which the text is created.
A thing or episode that is considered exemplary of a certain <fen>Type</fen>.
The category of things or events from which an <fen>Instance</fen> is picked out.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which is widely known and recognized.
The behavior, attribute, or associated entities that provide the reason for the <fen>Entity</fen> being famous.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is famous.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is famous.
listRoleExamples: This station is famous <fex>for the many ramen shacks surrounding it</fex>.
Certain people are well known <fex>only in North America</fex>.
